Figure Caption: (a) XRD patterns of mechanically alloyed powders as a function of milling time; (b) XRD patterns of SPS'ed and as-cast samples, with the pattern of the 49 h milled powders for comparison.
(a) SEM image of the 49 h milled powders; (b) EDS spectrum corresponding to (a).

TEM micrographs of the 49 h milled powders. (a) bright-field TEM image; (b) SAED pattern corresponding to (a); (c) statistical grain diameter distribution; (d) another bright-field TEM image; (e) HRTEM image of the circled area in (d). The area marked with a yellow square in (e) was subjected to fast Fourier transform (FFT), and the FFT pattern is displayed in (f), corresponding to a SAED pattern along the[1¯11]zone axis of an FCC structure. (For interpretation of the references to colour in this figure legend, the reader is referred to the web version of this article.)

TEM micrographs of the bulk nc Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA. (a) Bright-field TEM image showing nanoscale grains; (b) SAED pattern corresponding to (a), indicating an FCC structure; (c) bright-field TEM image showing nanoscale grains and ultrafine grains; (d) statistical grain diameter distribution.

(a) Bright-field TEM image of the bulk nc Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5 HEA showing nanoscale grains and ultrafine grains; (b) bright-field TEM image exhibiting twins in some UFGs; (c), (d) and (e) SAED patterns of ultrafine grain A along different zone axes, corresponding to SAED patterns of an FCC structure along [001], [011] and [112] zone axes, respectively.

(a) Bright-field TEM image of the bulk nc Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA exhibiting twins; and (b) SAED pattern of grain 1 in (a) along [011]M(matrix) and[01¯1¯]T(twin) zone axes; (c) statistical twin thickness distribution.
Microstructure of the bulk CG Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA. (a) OM image; (b) BSE image; (c) statistical grain diameter distribution.

(a) and (b) Bright-field TEM images of the bulk CG Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA; (c), (d) and (e) SAED patterns of the grain in (b) along different zone axes, corresponding to SAED patterns of an FCC structure along [001], [011] and [112] zone axes, respectively.

(a) Representative engineering stress–strain curves of the bulk nc and CG Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5samples after SPS and casting in compression, respectively; (b) compressive yield strength versus strain for the bulk nc Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA in comparison with those of FCC structured HEAs in the literature. #1 and #2 represent the bulk nc and CG Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5, respectively; #3–#9 correspond to as-cast CG Co20Ni20Fe20Cr20Cu20[10], Co18.2Ni18.2Fe18.2Cr18.2Ti9.0Cu18.2[10], Co18.2Ni18.2Fe18.2Cr18.2Al9.0Cu18.2[11], Co25Ni25Fe25Cr25[17], Co23.25Ni23.25Fe23.25Cr23.25Mo7.00[17], Co23.25Ni23.25Fe23.25Cr23.25Ti7.00[18], and Co29.41Ni29.41Fe29.42Al5.88Si5.88[19], respectively. #2, #3, #5 and #9 alloys were not fractured during compression tests.
(a) Dislocations in the 49 h milled Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA powders, (b) dislocations in the bulk nc Co25Ni25Fe25Al7.5Cu17.5HEA. “T” and arrows indicate dislocations.
